Define the 3 Ls levels for bits with key differentiators:

L0: Created to be inherited without actual real world usage (bit-database)
L1: Stateless, single-dependency/limited-dependencies, environment-agnostic, inherits L0, L1
L2: Service-specific auth, CRUD operations, webhook/trigger support, inherits L0,L1,L2, uses L0,L1
L3: Composes L0/L1/L2, business-focused, sensible defaults, built-in error handling



